  "prompt": "What changes do you want on Quora? Why?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't have personal preferences or desires. However, I can suggest potential changes to Quora based on common user feedback and discussions about improving user experience. Here are a few ideas:\n\n1. **Enhanced Moderation Tools**: Implement AI-driven tools to better identify and remove spam or low-quality content quickly, ensuring the platform remains informative and respectful.\n\n2. **Improved Answer Quality Controls**: Introduce a more robust system for upvoting or downvoting answers based on factual accuracy, allowing users to better discern reliable information.\n\n3. **User Customization Options**: Allow users to customize their feed more extensively, so they can follow specific topics, keywords, or types of content that interest them.\n\n4. **Better Notification System**: Develop a more nuanced notification system that highlights relevant answers, questions, and interactions without overwhelming users.\n\n5. **Expanded Categories and Topics**: Offer a wider range of categories or subcategories to help niche topics gain visibility and attract relevant expertise.\n\n6. **Incentives for High-Quality Contributions**: Consider rewards or recognition for users who consistently provide high-quality responses, encouraging a culture of expertise and helpfulness.\n\n7. **Enhanced Community Engagement Features**: Foster more interaction among users through features like Q&A sessions with experts or live discussions on trending topics.\n\nThese changes could help improve the overall quality of content on the platform and enhance user engagement.",
